19 NEW SECTION. Section 10. Legal remedies -- damages. (1) A pregnancy center or a party
20 aggrieved by a violation of [section 2] may commence a civil action for damages, declaratory relief, injunctive
21 relief, and any other appropriate relief.
22 (2) On a finding of a violation of [section 2], the prevailing party is entitled to recover actual
23 damages or statutory damages of $50,000, whichever is greater, plus attorney fees and costs. If the person
24 acted with malice, the court may award treble actual damages or treble statutory damages, whichever is
25 greater.
26 (3) Damages awarded under this section are cumulative and are not limited by other remedies that
27 may be available under federal or state law.
